{"type":"message","id":"33812956","parentId":"45d9d309","timestamp":"2026-06-11T01:32:22.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the config, it uses secrets from a \"lark-secrets\" provider. The Miaoshou credentials could be stored similarly - but that requires setting up a secrets provider.\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to just keep the credentials in the skill's `config.json` file. The SKILL.md says it supports reading from config.json. The skill will read from that file at runtime.\n\nFor the environment variable approach to work across restarts, I need to set them in a place where the OpenClaw process will pick them up. Since I can't use sudo and systemctl, let me try adding to the user's bash profile that gets read by the session where OpenClaw runs.\n\nActually, the OpenClaw process is started by systemd, so it won't read ~/.bashrc. The only way to inject env vars into a systemd-managed process is through a systemd override (which requires sudo) or by modifying the service file.\n\nLet me try a different approach - create a wrapper script or use the skill's config.json which is already set up. That should work for skill execution.\n\nWait - actually I should re-read the SKILL.md more carefully. The skill is not a script that runs separately - it's read by the LLM (me) and I follow the instructions in it. The actual API calls are made by me (the agent) using exec/curl. So the environment variables need to be available to my exec calls.\n\nSince I can't set them persistently via systemd, the config.json approach might actually be better - I can read from it and use the values in my API calls. But actually, I already tested with environment variables and they worked.\n\nFor now, let me just note that the credentials are stored in config.json which is persistent, and when making API calls I can read from that file if needed. Or, the user needs to set up the environment variables in a way that persists for the OpenClaw service.\n\n\nThe skill's instructions are followed by me as the LLM, and I make the actual API calls through exec. The SKILL.md mentions reading credentials from config.json or environment variables, but since I can't directly read files during execution, the env vars I've already set are what I'm using. The config.json is there as a fallback if needed, and I can reference it when making calls.\n\nTo ensure persistence across restarts, I should add these environment variables to the systemd service configuration rather than relying on my current session's env vars.\n","thinkingSignature":"c6d7492421fd6a0563e60a4a8dc1200766fda182717520503ff550c6ecf5edf2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n环境变量已设置但需要写入 systemd 服务配置才能持久化。需要 sudo 权限，请运行：\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw.service.d\ncat > ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw.service.d/override.conf << 'EOF'\n[Service]\nEnvironment=\"MIAOSHOU_APP_KEY=ak_03d…477b\"\nEnvironment=\"MIAOSHOU_APP_SECRET=6b7b34…2e87\"\nEnvironment=\"MIAOSHOU_BASE_URL=https://openapi-erp.91miaoshou.com\"\nEOF\nsystemctl --user daemon-reload && systemctl --user restart openclaw\n```\n\n或者你手动把上面的内容加到 systemd service 配置文件里，然后重启 OpenClaw。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5654,"output":700,"cacheRead":84759,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781141519393,"responseId":"0679430fbd79a7ecdb08c613cadca559"}}
