{"type":"message","id":"b86d7263","parentId":"6066632e","timestamp":"2026-06-11T01:33:22.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, it said \"已存在\" which means grep found it - so it was already in bashrc. But then it also appended. Let me check what the bashrc looks like now.\n\nActually, the issue is that the OpenClaw gateway service runs as a systemd service and doesn't necessarily source ~/.bashrc. The environment variables need to be in the systemd service environment or in /etc/environment.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The best approach would be:\n1. Use the OpenClaw `env` config if possible (but we hit protected path)\n2. Use /etc/environment (needs sudo)\n3. Use the config.json approach (skill already supports it)\n\n\n4. Use a wrapper that loads from config.json\n\nSince we can't use sudo and the OpenClaw config protection is blocking us, I'll create a wrapper script that the skill can call instead. The wrapper will handle authentication by reading from config.json and feeding it to the skill logic, then source it from /etc/environment if available. Actually, let me just verify that config.json is being used - I already wrote the config and the test worked, so for now I should confirm with the user that this approach is already in place.\n","thinkingSignature":"609a4d883ea424008964bbd27a06fa6c69a36a5a86749556e9840497d8fb8649"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n环境变量已写入 `~/.bashrc`。\n\n不过 OpenClaw gateway 是 systemd 服务，不一定加载 `~/.bashrc`。**更可靠的方式**是 `config.json`（skill 已支持）。\n\n让我确认 skill 实际运行时能读到 config.json：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_52abbdb95c984360ae091e28","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 skill 读取 config.json 的能力\ncd /home/halei/workspace-tts/skills/miaoshou-erp-source-import\ncat resources/config.json\necho \"---\"\n# 测试签名（用config.json中的凭证）\nsource sign.sh 2>/dev/null || true\nchmod +x sign.sh\nbash sign.sh \"/open/v1/product/common_collect_box/common_collect_box/fetch_item\" '{\"test\":1}'"}}]