{"type":"message","id":"caff47fd","parentId":"4b73053e","timestamp":"2026-06-11T01:34:13.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the key information is persisted/stored persistently. They're asking about whether the config we set up will persist across restarts.\n\nFrom what I can see:\n1. `config.json` in the skill directory - this IS persisted (it's a file)\n2. Environment variables in `~/.bashrc` - these will persist across restarts\n\nBut the issue is that OpenClaw gateway is running as a systemd service, and it may not load `~/.bashrc` environment variables.\n\nThe safest answer is: the `config.json` file is persisted (it's a file on disk). The environment variables in `~/.bashrc` will persist but may not be loaded by the systemd service.\n\nActually, looking at the message more carefully - they're asking from the Feishu DM channel, and the user is ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68. This seems to be coming through correctly.\n\nLet me think about what \"持久化存储\" means here - is the key info stored persistently? The answer is:\n- config.json: YES, it's a file\n- bashrc env vars: YES, but may not apply to the systemd service\n\nBut actually, I notice the config.json I wrote has the secret partially masked (\"6b7b34…2e87\"). The actual secret is \"6b7b3413d16f4c09836722af3d44111f7a4422956a3a4e7393ed48c20d6e2e87\". I wrote it with \"6b7b34…2e87\" which is wrong. The API calls earlier worked though, so either the config.json wasn't being used, or the sign.sh script wasn't actually reading from config.json...\n\nWait, looking back at the earlier API call that succeeded, I used environment variables in the exec command directly, not the config.json. \n\nThe config.json has the secret masked with \"6b7b34…2e87\" which is NOT the real secret. But the test that succeeded was because I used environment variables directly in the exec command with the actual secret. The sign.sh script was written but I never tested it with the real credentials. The real issue is that the config.json file is masking the secret, so it won't actually work for authentication.\n","thinkingSignature":"8e4dc1a5410dc044d01171c94d373d70ad70d3d62394d84fbc91275e5fdc5e85"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nconfig.json 是文件，持久化存储在磁盘上，可以被 skill 读取。\n\n但我注意到 `config.json` 里 secret 被截断了（`6b7b34…2e87`），不是完整值。之前成功的测试是因为我在命令行直接用了完整 secret。\n\n让我修复 config.json：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_227fa60e5c3f44a58a4dece2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/workspace-tts/skills/miaoshou-erp-source-import/resources/config.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6482,"output":589,"cacheRead":83928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90999,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781141632078,"responseId":"067943803d091411a0963b798b99e829"}}
