{"type":"message","id":"7deb02e7","parentId":"7ae65174","timestamp":"2026-06-11T01:34:29.281Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the config.json actually has the full secret. I was confused earlier - looking at the read output it shows the full secret. The \"6b7b34…2e87\" I saw in my write command was just how I was describing it in prose, but the actual file content has the full value.\n\nSo the config.json IS correctly stored with the full secret. The skill can read this file and use it for authentication.\n\nThe remaining concern is: will the skill actually READ this config.json when it runs? Looking at the SKILL.md, it says:\n- \"Configure credentials in one of these ways: Copy resources/config.json.example to resources/config.json and fill app_key and app_secret\"\n- \"Or set environment variables MIAOSHOU_APP_KEY and MIAOSHOU_APP_SECRET\"\n\nSo the skill should support config.json. The question is whether the skill code actually implements this reading. The SKILL.md says it supports both, so I assume it does.\n\nFor persistence: config.json is a file on disk, it persists across restarts. Environment variables in bashrc also persist but may not apply to systemd services.\n\nI should confirm to the user that:\n1. config.json has the correct full credentials\n2. It will persist because it's a file\n","thinkingSignature":"aaf2c335aab0fef76a4ca54d9e995c27e0458e475f72bd7ca6f0f8fa1dd435a0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nconfig.json 里 secret 是完整值，已正确存储：\n\n```\napp_key: ak_03d60381f9ed401b9e825942864a477b\napp_secret: 6b7b34...2e87 (完整值)\nbase_url: https://openapi-erp.91miaoshou.com\n```\n\n**持久化状态：**\n- ✅ `config.json` — 文件存储，重启后仍在\n- ✅ `~/.bashrc` 里的环境变量 — 持久，但 systemd 服务可能不加载\n\n**建议：** 保持 config.json 即可，skill 支持从文件读取凭证。如果后续 skill 重启后用不了，再考虑通过 `systemctl --user set-environment` 设置服务级环境变量。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5370,"output":414,"cacheRead":85748,"cacheWrite