{"type":"message","id":"000fc14d","parentId":"c7a4ace6","timestamp":"2026-06-11T01:34:46.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the config.json file just needs to exist and stay there. They're asking if it will work as a persistent storage for the credentials.\n\nThe answer is yes - the config.json file on disk is persistent. However, the issue is that the `app_secret` in the config.json I wrote earlier was truncated (I used `6b7b34…2e87` instead of the full secret `6b7b3413d16f4c09836722af3d44111f7a4422956a3a4e7393ed48c20d6e2e87`).\n\nWait, looking back at the conversation, the user provided the full secret in an earlier message:\n\n\n- app_secret: \"6b7b34…2e87\"\n\nBut when I wrote the config.json, I used `6b7b34…2e87` (truncated). This was a mistake. However, the test API call earlier succeeded because I had the full secret in my exec command environment.\n\nSo the user is asking: will the config.json just work as-is? The answer is NO - because the secret in config.json is truncated, it won't work. I need to update the config.json with the complete secret.\n","thinkingSignature":"b24b89b5f83a37497b8d59159cbbfc8b12e09050ba7a075fd78b445077e6cc5c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nconfig.json 是持久化的，但有个问题 — 之前写入的 `app_secret` 被截断了：\n\n```\napp_secret: \"***\"  ← 不完整，实际是 6b7b3413d16f4c09836722af3d44111f7a4422956a3a4e7393ed48c20d6e2e87\n```\n\n之前测试能成功是因为 exec 命令里直接用了完整 secret，不是从 config.json 读的。\n\n需要我更新 config.json 为完整 secret 吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5343,"output":411,"cacheRead":85384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91138,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781141670605,"responseId":"067943a777a5f43777c39f3f34ac9f44"}}
